title: For Sale:  Draco AK47 (AK-47) Rifle, custom build, very high quality, carbine conversion, CA legal w/kydex gripwrap
postcontent: ***Call anytime before 11PM REDACTED Brian  (Serious inquiries only, no emails, thanks!)***  Got a very hard to find firearm for our good old state of CA here... a prestine custom converted Draco rifle!  At it's heart the Draco is a 11.75" barrelled 'pistol' and is a perfect candidate for your SBR conversion, if you make the move out of this ridiculous state we live in.  Starting as a Draco pistol, this carbine rifle conversion has a faux suppressor/barrel extension threaded onto the 14/1LH threads, which is pinned and tack welded in place to bring it up to the legal carbine rifle barrel length...  With a simple drill bit and a dremel tool you can easily remove the barrel extension though to expose the AK's 14/1LH threads for your favorite muzzle device, which leaves you with a nice, short little SBR package (of course where SBR's are legal and the appropriate NFA paperwork is filed, in other words, when ya get the heck out of the BS state of CA!)  The rifle's stock is a nice manticore folder, however, for CA purposes, the stock's hinge is removed and the buttstock itself is bolted on using the same mounting point as the hinge.  With purchase, the hinge will be included separately (as shown installed in pics for pre-ban style folding stock set-up) so you can change it out when you feel ready to do so, just unbolt the stock, and re-bolt on the stock with the hinge attached, that simple.  The parts aren't illegal to own, but with the new lame laws you just can't run around with a folding or collapsible stock anymore here in wonderful commufornia, but like I mentioned, I'll be happy to include them separately when you buy the rifle.  Mag is also a blocked 10/30 (10rnd capacity) with floorplate sealed in place for CA compliance.  This thing is BRAND NEW, perfect condition, has a very nice manganese phosphate base coat with teflon top coat finish and is an all mil-spec rifle... Yes!  Unlike other AK's, since these things are imported into the US as pistols, they aren't subject to 922R upon import.  When the conversion was professionally done prior to bringing it into CA, the simple addition of a tapco G2 trigger group (great trigger), the stock, foregrip, pistol grip (which also has the CA legal kydex grip wrap installed, see pic for example since the main pic I chose to put up is of the rifle's free-state configuration), and the barrel extension all count for 922R compliance.  This rifle is the real deal, totally legit, and my local FFL here in Paradise is happy to facilitate the private party transfer for you, just outside of Chico, CA.  There may also be some shops in Chico who will facilitate the transfer too, but I've noticed that since the law changed, some CA gun shops have just all together stopped helping transfer any 'black rifles', since they don't understand what 'featureless' means.  This rifle, with the grip wrap, fixed stock conversion, and no flash hider falls within the featureless category.  Our local, biggest gun/archery shop here in town is a well established, reputable shop that also has tons of black rifle accessories still up for sale which you can't find at corporate big-box stores in the city.  They've also got the new AR set-up with the quick-release takedown pin which legally allows you to actuate a special mag-release that actually functions faster than the old 'bullet-buttton' style AR work-around, NICE!!!    So, give me a call anytime, I'd be happy to meet up and show ya the rifle.  Thanks again!

The rifle's stock is a nice manticore folder, however, for CA purposes, the stock's hinge is removed and the buttstock itself is bolted on using the same mounting point as the hinge.  With purchase, the hinge will be included (as shown installed in pics for pre-ban style folding stock set-up) so you can change it out when you feel ready to do so, just unbolt the stock, and re-bolt on the stock with the hinge attached, that simple.  The parts aren't illegal to own, but with the new lame laws you just can't run around with a folding or collapsible stock anymore here in wonderful commufornia, but like I mentioned, I'll be happy to include them separately when you buy the rifle.  Mag is also a blocked 10/30 (10rnd capacity) with floorplate sealed in place for CA compliance.  This thing is BRAND NEW, perfect condition, has a very nice manganese phosphate base coat with teflon top coated finish and is an all mil-spec rifle... Yes!  Unlike other AK's, since these things are imported into the US as pistols, they aren't subject to 922R upon import.  When the conversion was professionally done prior to bringing it into CA, the simple addition of a tapco G2 trigger group (great trigger), the stock, foregrip, pistol grip (which also has the CA legal kydex grip wrap installed, see pic for example since the main pic I chose to put up is of the rifle's free-state configuration), and the barrel extension all count for 922R compliance.  This rifle is the real deal, totally legit, and my local FFL here in Paradise is happy to facilitate the private party transfer for you, just outside of Chico, CA.  There may also be some shops in Chico who will facilitate the transfer too, but I've noticed that since the law changed, some CA gun shops have just all together stopped helping transfer any 'black rifles', since they don't understand what 'featureless' means.  This rifle, with the grip wrap, fixed stock conversion, and no flash hider falls within the featureless category.  Our local, biggest gun/archery shop here in town is a well established, reputable shop that also has tons of black rifle accessories still up for sale which you can't find at corporate big-box stores in the city.  They've also got the new AR set-up with the quick-release takedown pin which legally allows you to actuate a special mag-release that actually functions faster than the old 'bullet-buttton' style AR work-around, NICE!!!    So, give me a call anytime, I'd be happy to meet up with ya.  Thanks again!

title: For Sale:  Premier Four Gun 1911 Photography & Display Stands
postcontent:
Have you ever struggled how to display or photograph the "quadruplets" in your collection?My Quad 1911 Display / Photography Stand presents 4 of your favorite 1911's onto a decorative oak base.   I am ALWAYS willing to discuss with you any custom options / sizes / configurations that you might need.  Some of my customers want a mix of full size and officers size magazine posts to match their collection.  I can do that no problem.  Customized orders will add 5 to 6 days to your shipping time, as I need to construct and polyurethane your unique stand individually.  My stands come stock with full size 1911 magazine posts.My 1911 display, photography, and storage stands are all individually hand crafted . . . . mainly because I don’t have a full-epic wood shop filled with CNC routers, industrial table saws, manly drill presses, electrostatic paint booths, planers, CNC controlled lathes, and/or other testosterone fueled toolage.  You see, wood crafting is a hobby which is new to me, and dovetails I think, perfectly with my other passion - collecting 1911 style pistols.Because of the above (and because I don’t use "genetically engineered wood") you will find the occasional “craftsman finger print” in my creations. There might be slight irregularities in the wood and/or minute differences in the assembly or finish from piece to piece.  I will never send out anything I would regard as a “second” or “blem” without stating so and pricing accordingly.Right now I am using the nicest, furniture grade, solid oak I can source. I might be able to get some more exotic woods in the near future, but for now, these are oak.  I hand paint each of these stands with a nice marine-grade polyurethane so the natural beauty and grain of the wood stands out.  I sand them after each layer of polyurethane and re-coat until I achieve a nice hard protective finish.Of course, any firearms shown in my listings are to illustrate the items intended use and are NOT included in the sale.
I have many more sizes and configurations to suite your needs.
